# 1. Introduction  
This project analyzes a student performance dataset.  
Goals of this analysis:

- Explore descriptive statistics  
- Visualize key academic performance indicators  
- Understand relationships between variables  
- Build a machine learning model to predict student scores  

All dataset exploration, plots, and ML outputs come from Python execution.

---

# 2. Dataset Description  

The dataset contains **600 rows** and **10 columns**:  

| Variable | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| gender | Student gender |
| race_ethnicity | Ethnic group |
| parental_education | Parent's education level |
| lunch | Lunch type |
| test_preparation | Whether test prep was completed |
| math_score | Math exam score |
| reading_score | Reading exam score |
| writing_score | Writing exam score |
| study_hours | Weekly study hours |
| avg_score | Average of math, reading, and writing |

### ğŸ“Œ Dataset Shape  

### ğŸ“Œ Head of the dataset  
Displayed in notebook output.

---

# 3. Descriptive Statistics  

Key observations:

- Average scores mostly range between **60 and 90**.
- Study hours vary widely.
- Reading and writing scores are strongly correlated.
- Overall performance is relatively high.

---

